{{ahnentafel bottom}}
Emeric's wife, [[Constance of Aragon, Holy Roman Empress|Constance]], was the daughter of King [[Alfonso II of Aragon]].{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|p=225, Appendix 4}} Their marriage took place between 1196 and 1200.{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|p=225, Appendix 4}}{{sfn|<U+00C9>rszegi|Solymosi|1981|p=125}} Their only known child, Ladislaus, was born around 1200 and died on 7 May 1205.{{sfn|Krist<U+00F3>|Makk|1996|p=228, Appendix 4}} Queen Constance, who outlived both her husband and their son, eventually became the first wife of the future [[Frederick II, Holy Roman Emperor]].{{sfn|Engel|2001|p=89}}

